Fix `rax2 -a` exit code  The `rax2 -a` command was exiting with a status code of 1, which caused issues with tools that interpret a non-zero exit code as an error.  This was happening because the `-a` flag handler in `libr/main/rax2.c` was returning `0` (false), which was incorrectly interpreted as a failure.  This commit changes the return value to `true` to correctly indicate success, resulting in an exit code of 0.
